CLOCK TONGUE

clock_tongue runs at 100 Hz, the gustatory sampling rate
taste receptors are slower than touch because the molecular recognition takes time
fast enough to register flavor as it appears in the mouth, slow enough that brief sensations register cleanly

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe zest_heartbeat.zc
observe clock_master.rana
observe tongue.rana

the 7 properties of clock_tongue:
1 ENERGY zero point nine
2 PHASE zero point one
3 SPIN zero point three
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point six with master

VERB tick_at_100Hz
divide master by 480 to produce 100 Hz

VERB sample_taste
on each tick, sample the tongue's taste receptors for sweet, sour, salty, bitter, umami
the samples flow to the gustatory cortex

a tongue clock is matched to the speed of biological flavor detection
fast taste reactions still feel responsive at 100 Hz
